DATA CLOUD
Find Segments in Marketing Cloud Engagement

After you create and activate segments to Marketing Cloud Engagement, view them in Contact Builder. A Data Cloud segments subfolder is created when you publish your first activation.

You can access the

Engagement

folders only in the Business Unit (BU) that your

Engagement

user is associated with. In

Engagement

, you can see the Data Cloud segments for that BU in Contact Builder.

In Marketing Cloud, click Contact Builder.
Click Data Extensions.
Click Shared Items.
Click Shared Data Extensions.
Click Customer 360 Segments.

Segments are created as a shared data extension with this naming format: {segmentName_activationName_segmentID_activationID}. In Shared Data Extensions, if the segment is activated to more than one BU, the activated segments are created as a shared data extension in the Data Cloud subfolder. For the activation target, the shared data extension folder is based on the selected BUs. Child business units (MID) provide permission to the parent business unit (EID) by default. Any shared data extensions created on the MID can be accessed by the EID.

If the number of individuals in your

Engagement

segment is lower than the segment population in Data Cloud, try troubleshooting with tips from this knowledge article: Data Cloud segment counts do not match activation counts for a Marketing Cloud activation target.
